The latest MSTest is **4.2.3**. Here are the breaking changes relevant to your project:

---

## 1. `[ExpectedException]` is removed (critical for your code)

This attribute no longer exists in v4. Replace with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>`:

```csharp
// Before
[ExpectedException(typeof(ArgumentNullException))]
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Validate(null);
}

// After
[TestMethod]
public void Validate_NullInput_ThrowsArgumentNull()
{
    Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentNullException>(() => Validate(null));
}
```

## 2. `Assert.IsTrue(true)` triggers warning MSTEST0032

Your `Validate_ValidInput_Succeeds` test will produce a warning since the condition is always true. Replace with a meaningful assertion or suppress it.

## 3. Other notable v4 breaking changes (may not affect you now)

| Change | Impact |
|--------|--------|
| `ClassCleanupBehavior` enum removed | Remove parameter from `[ClassCleanup]` |
| `TestContext.Properties` is now `IDictionary<string, object>` | Use `.ContainsKey()` instead of `.Contains()` |
| `Assert.ThrowsException` removed | Use `Assert.ThrowsExactly` |
| Assert `message` + `params object[]` → just `message` | Use string interpolation |
| Min TFM is .NET 8 | You're fine on net8.0 |
| `TestTimeout` enum removed | Use `[Timeout(int.MaxValue)]` |
| `TestContext.ManagedType` removed | Use `FullyQualifiedTestClassName` |

---

Would you like me to apply the fixes to your test file?
